      • isIdMandatory

        boolean isIdMandatory()
        This method can be used to query if the identifier of this NamedSBase is required to be defined (i.e., not null) in the definition of SBML.
        Returns:
        true if the identifier of this element must be set in order to create a valid SBML representation. false otherwise, i.e., if the identifier can be understood as an optional attribute.
